==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Cottier
<hw>Cot"ti*er</hw> <pr>(-t⟦icr⟧*⟦etil⟧r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OF.
<ets>cotier</ets>. See <er>Coterie</er>, and cf. <er>Cotter</er>.]</ety>
<def>In Great Britain and Ireland, a person who hires a small cottage,
with or without a plot of land. Cottiers commonly aid in the work of the
landlord's farm.</def> <altsp>[Written also <asp>cottar</asp> and
<asp>cotter</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cottise</ent>⟦br⟧
